window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From </b><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> bestseller Pepper Winters comes a green-flag stalker standalone romance.</b></p> <p><b>I have a stalker.</b></p> <p>A masked man who watches me from the shadows. A guardian who says he's there to protect me—to help me heal from almost dying at the hands of another man.</p> <p>He says he's willing to do anything to help me move on. That I needn't be afraid of him.</p> <p>I agree to keep him my secret and share how much I'm truly struggling.</p> <p>In return, he guards me. Even if it means guarding me from himself.</p> <p><b>I've known her my entire life.</b></p> <p>She's the girl next door with whom I share a childhood betrothal thanks to our two grandmothers wishing to turn their lifelong friendship into family.</p> <p>I'm also the doctor who tended to her in the ER after her ex tried to kill her. I want to help her in any way I can, but I also know she'll never accept my help because I'm the reason he tried to kill her in the first place.</p> <p>But I can't stand by and see her suffer, so… I come up with a plan.</p> <p>A highly illegal plan that ends with me breaking laws, rules, and my own heart...</p> <p>Texting Dr. Stalker is a standalone and features <i>a girl next door and a Doctor who would do anything to keep her safe; childhood friends-to-lovers; a green-flag stalker; hidden identity; and a masked protector.</i></p> <p><i>Narrated in duet style.</i></p>"; 
